Already compelling.</i>

03:04.779 --> 03:07.924
<i>"Five layers of wool
and oilskin enclosed him."</i>

03:11.642 --> 03:12.642
You asleep?

03:15.530 --> 03:18.030
I've been holding
that in since Jeopardy.

03:21.691 --> 03:24.558
- What's all that, Dick?
- I'm watching every movie ever made,

03:24.683 --> 03:26.831
alphabetically by actor's last name.

03:27.305 --> 03:29.927
I'm on Martin Mull.
Underrated actor.

03:30.052 --> 03:33.235
Could anyone else have played
Colonel Mustard in <i>Clue</i> ?

03:33.360 --> 03:35.727
The answer is yes.
Christopher Lloyd.

03:35.852 --> 03:38.351
My point is, Mull gets work.

03:38.476 --> 03:39.626
Consistently.

03:40.096 --> 03:42.219
But you have a wife
and kids at home.

03:42.344 --> 03:45.260
How do you have the free time
to do... anything?

03:46.336 --> 03:48.647
The boys down at
the lab gave me these.

03:48.772 --> 03:52.273
You take a pill right before bed,
and you feel like you slept 8 hours.

03:52.514 --> 03:54.013
So you take these pills,

03:54.138 --> 03:56.318
and you never have to sleep?

03:57.020 --> 03:58.754
So I can spend days with my family,

03:58.879 --> 04:00.692
and the nights are all for me.

04:00.817 --> 04:03.059
What will the guys at the lab
think of next?

04:03.184 --> 04:04.931
They have tons of cool stuff.

04:05.056 --> 04:06.742
Check out my rocket zipper.

04:09.938 --> 04:12.224
Once again, we beat the Russians.

04:23.424 --> 04:24.524
I feel so...

04:25.318 --> 04:26.733
not wired, but...

04:26.901 --> 04:28.001
well-rested.

04:28.324 --> 04:30.830
Like I had a small coffee
around 6:30 at night.

04:30.955 --> 04:32.305
I'm feeling good.

04:33.887 --> 04:36.108
<i>This is the song
that I wrote at 3:00 a.m.</i>

04:36.569 --> 04:39.236
<i>I taught myself
how to play the guitar</i>

04:39.567 --> 04:42.239
<i>I only know two chords so far</i>

04:42.407 --> 04:45.119
<i>My fingers hurt 'cause
I haven't grown calluses</i>

