I was the pool boy
and the pizza guy.

15:27.347 --> 15:30.092
If demonstrating that
the working poor need two jobs

15:30.217 --> 15:32.215
just to make ends meet
isn't modern or real,

15:32.340 --> 15:34.391
then I don't know what the hell is!

15:41.209 --> 15:42.607
So many soil coins!

15:43.071 --> 15:45.713
- Dad, you gotta eat.
- I have Pirate Booty.

15:47.179 --> 15:48.999
I gotta practice.
Championship's tonight.

15:49.124 --> 15:51.764
I got another e-mail from Mom.
Expedition's going well.

15:51.889 --> 15:53.921
- She said...
- Did she say there's a nuclear rabbit

15:54.046 --> 15:56.207
on her expedition,
because I just froze 4.

15:56.738 --> 15:57.922
Just thawed out!

15:58.549 --> 15:59.649
Oh, got 'em!

16:01.127 --> 16:03.503
{\EASTERN REGIONAL
BEETMAN CHAMPIONSHIPS}

16:04.475 --> 16:05.784
You're going down, Trung.

16:05.909 --> 16:07.881
You forgot to aerate your soil!

16:15.709 --> 16:17.578
Trung, you've got two options:

16:17.703 --> 16:19.449
You can hang your head in shame

16:19.574 --> 16:23.064
or you can shake my hand
and buy me a slice like a man.

16:25.124 --> 16:26.124
Coward.

16:27.464 --> 16:30.196
And the winner of the Eastern
Regional Beetman Tournament:

16:30.372 --> 16:31.372
Stan Smith!

16:31.796 --> 16:33.178
Benny, hurry up!

16:33.303 --> 16:35.551
We have to pick your brother up
at karate!

16:35.676 --> 16:37.298
Okay, Mom!

16:37.423 --> 16:39.973
- I hate her!
- Geez, take it easy, kid.

16:44.668 --> 16:46.847
See, that's why you lost, Trung:
your lady.

16:46.972 --> 16:49.833
You didn't train enough because you were
spending too much time with her,

16:49.958 --> 16:52.126
having dinner, watching TV,

16:53.645 --> 16:56.490
picking out her shoes
for a cocktail party.

17:08.934 --> 17:10.996
What is it?
What is it?

17:11.742 --> 17:13.627
Don't stop.
A little more.

17:14.586 --> 17:15.736
Almost there!

17:17.421 --> 17:18.857
Right in my face.

17:18.982 --> 17:21.665
Great, now it's gonna
be freezing in here.

17:23.386 --> 17:25.907
Steve, come on. We're going
to the diner to write porn.

17:26.032 --> 17:28.214
I was just getting my sweater
in case it gets chilly.

17:28.339 --> 17:29.340
A sweater?!

17:29.465 --> 17:31.000
What are you, an old lady?

17:36.454 --> 17:39.813
Better to have it and not need it
than to need it and not have it.

17:41.134 --> 17:43.218
Oh, my God, I'm gonna get you!

17:46.124 --> 17:48.434
- I can't believe you!
- Yeah, how's that taste?

17:48.559 --> 17:49.972
That taste good!

17:51.799 --> 17:53.758
It's so obvious!

17:54.104 --> 17:56.252
Interior: Chimdale Spa.

17:58.821 --> 18:01.685
I shouldn't have had
that second glass of champagne.

18:02.162 --> 18:04.097
I'm feeling vulnerable.

18:04.222 --> 18:07.806
Good, 'cause I've been dying
to kiss you all night.

18:16.382 --> 18:20.133
You gotta to be kidding me!
H.P. said no more sci-fi stuff!

18:20.258 --> 18:25.216
When will you people realize
that robots are erotic?

18:25.686 --> 18:28.245
I don't know. Maybe this business
has changed too much.

18:28.370 --> 18:31.366
Did you know I read that they bleach
buttholes now, Steven?

18:31.491 --> 18:34.039
Are they trying to say
God chose the wrong color?

18:35.502 --> 18:37.449
Maybe we don't know
anything about sex.

18:37.618 --> 18:40.590
Maybe we should just stick
to writing something we do know.

18:41.787 --> 18:43.347
A light romantic comedy...

18:43.472 --> 18:45.957
Set in turn-of-the- century England!

18:46.093 --> 18:47.459
"Exterior, Manor House.

18:47.864 --> 18:50.272
"As the pizza delivery man
emerges from his carriage

18:50.397 --> 18:53.592
"and rings the doorbell.
The robot butler answers the door."

18:53.717 --> 18:56.755
Love it! Still waiting on
that tuna melt, sweetheart!

18:57.132 --> 18:59.997
My memory chip does not
register ordering a pizza.

19:00.320 --> 19:01.880
Prank sensor activated.

19:02.005 --> 19:04.677
That's dialogue!
You just pitched dialogue!

19:07.699 --> 19:09.230
Francine, what do you see?

19:10.258 --> 19:13.215
I see coral, some plant life,

19:13.612 --> 19:15.685
but I don't see the Colossal Squid.

19:16.063 --> 19:17.071
Wait a second.

19:21.478 --> 19:23.620
The Colossal Squid.

19:33.765 --> 19:36.278
Stan, don't turn around.
Just swim away.

19:42.565 --> 19:45.760
Stan, you just killed
the Colossal Squid!

19:45.933 --> 19:47.867
<i>No, I don't think so.
That one was tiny.</i>

19:47.992 --> 19:50.799
<i>I passed, like, five others on the way
over here that were way bigger.</i>

19:50.924 --> 19:53.817
- <i>If anything, I killed a baby.</i>
- What are you doing here?

19:54.047 --> 19:56.395
<i>I came to tell you that I was wrong.</i>

19:56.668 --> 19:58.974
<i>I know I said I wanted time alone,</i>

19:59.099 --> 20:01.658
<i>but now I realize
I just want time with you.</i>

20:01.909 --> 20:03.409
Things have changed, Stan.

20:03.654 --> 20:06.838
<i>They don't have to!
I threw away the pills, Francine.</i>

20:06.963 --> 20:08.539
<i>I want to go back to our old life,</i>

20:08.834 --> 20:12.335
<i>being with you during the day
and sleeping with you at night.</i>

20:16.760 --> 20:17.797
There you are.

20:17.922 --> 20:20.190
You switched channels on me,
you absurd madame.

20:20.315 --> 20:22.165
So, did you find zee squid?

20:22.721 --> 20:26.093
Remember, when you do find it,
we will tour zee world.

20:26.357 --> 20:28.655
Your life will change forever.

20:33.333 --> 20:34.921
I'm sorry, Philippe.

20:35.230 --> 20:36.930
I didn't find the squid.

20:37.501 --> 20:38.444
I was wrong.

20:42.369 --> 20:43.718
Fabien, my brother,

20:43.843 --> 20:47.210
we have wasted the money from the sale
of your bicycle company.

20:47.335 --> 20:48.585
You are ruined.

20:52.209 --> 20:53.209
Life, ah?

20:54.762 --> 20:57.112
Honey, turn your CB to channel nine.

21:05.760 --> 21:07.046
It's just the baby.

21:07.171 --> 21:08.958
It's the already-dead baby.

